node.text:
Wabi Sabi ... Rough textures, cracked walls, peeled paints, faded hues, frayed edges, dilapidated buildings, broken windows, rusty hinges, chipped tea cups ~ finding beauty in all of these marks of passing time... that is the Japanese philosophy of wabi sabi.
.
Wabi sabi urges you to take a pause from your relentless pursuit of perfection in life and celebrate the way things are rather than how they should be! .
How relevant is that in today’s context?? Uncanny isn’t it ?
